The paper deals with image retrieval using deep convolutional features, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed method involves unsupervised aggregation of features, which could also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of adaptive Gaussian filter and element-value sensitive vector suggests a focus on signal processing (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
